<h1 class="text-center text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl xl:text-6xl font-light leading-tight"
    style="font-family: 'Pacifico', cursive;">
    Bits of Ether
</h1>

<div class="flex justify-center w-full pt-4">
    <img class="w-16" src="/images/logo.png" alt="Cover image">
</div>

<p class="text-center mb-4 text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-4xl font-light leading-tight">
    <br>
    Freelance engineering <br> and software development.<br>
    <!-- Data pipelines.<br>
    Business process automation and innovation.<br>
    System modelling & token engineering.<br> -->
</p>

<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center -mx-2 -my-2 mb-8">
    <div class="flex justify-center w-full sm:w-1/3 px-2 py-2">
        <div class="max-w-sm w-full">
            <div class="shadow-lg text-white bg-sea-green rounded-b rounded p-2 flex flex-col justify-between leading-normal">
                <div class="font-bold text-lg">Application Development</div>
                <p class="text-base mb-2">
                    Phoenix and React are my frameworks of choice. I also have the DevOps and containerization experience to develop a robust and reliable system.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center w-full sm:w-1/3 px-2 py-2">
        <div class="max-w-sm w-full">
            <div class="shadow-lg text-white bg-sea-green rounded-b rounded p-2 flex flex-col justify-between leading-normal">
                <div class="font-bold text-lg">Engineering</div>
                <p class="text-base mb-2">
                    Systems engineering, token engineering, problem solving - building context from a background in mechatronics, control systems, and electronics.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center w-full sm:w-1/3 px-2 py-2">
        <div class="max-w-sm w-full">
            <div class="shadow-lg text-white bg-sea-green bg-orange-500 rounded p-2 flex flex-col justify-between leading-normal">
                <div class="font-bold text-lg">MVPs</div>
                <p class="text-base mb-2">
                    Using agile workflows, a broad technical skill set, and product development market knowledge, I can quickly develop proof-of-concepts.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center w-full sm:w-1/3 px-2 py-2">
        <div class="max-w-sm w-full">
            <div class="shadow-lg text-white bg-sea-green bg-orange-500 rounded p-2 flex flex-col justify-between leading-normal">
                <div class="font-bold text-lg">Data Pipelines</div>
                <p class="text-base mb-2">
                    Businesses are transitioning into the data economy. 
                    The scalability of companies like Uber depends on being able to
                    access and analyze data. I'll help you extract value from your business data.
                    Case study coming soon!
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex justify-center w-full sm:w-1/3 px-2 py-2">
        <div class="max-w-sm w-full">
            <div class="shadow-lg text-white bg-sea-green bg-orange-500 rounded p-2 flex flex-col justify-between leading-normal">
                <div class="font-bold text-lg">Process Automation</div>
                <p class="text-base mb-2">
                    Whether it's suplementing your existing processes with machine learning,
                    or incrementally automating tasks, technology can help you make your business more efficient.
                    I've managed production CI/CD pipelines and love improving developer tooling and experience.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<%= render "_tags.html", tags: @tags, conn: @conn %>

<div class="mb-8">
    <p class="font-sans text-grey-dark">
        I'm a freelance software developer,
        with an engineering background and a strong problem solving skill set.
        If you'd like to work with me on a problem or project, don't hesitate to drop me an
        <a href="<%= Routes.email_path(@conn, :index) %>">e-mail</a>.
    </p>
</div>

